msgid "Creating an Infinispan Server cluster in OpenShift has never been easier! We've just given the OpenShift templates for Infinispan server their biggest makeover yet which should help both Infinispan and OpenShift users:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2018-11-12-the-fastest-path-to-running-infinispan.adoc:22
msgid "The https://github.com/infinispan/infinispan-openshift-templates[repository] has been simplified and flattened out to only leave essential information. https://www.okd.io/minishift/[Minishift] is the preferred way to get started with Infinispan and OpenShift, so we've tailored the instructions for this set up."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2018-11-12-the-fastest-path-to-running-infinispan.adoc:28
msgid "OpenShift templates are now https://github.com/infinispan/infinispan-openshift-templates/blob/master/infinispan-ephemeral.yaml[YAML based] which is less verbose, but more importantly, allows Infinispan Server XML configuration to be shown as-is. This makes it easier to directly modify the XML in the template itself."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2018-11-12-the-fastest-path-to-running-infinispan.adoc:34
msgid "The fastest way to get started with Infinispan and OpenShift is to simply fire up Minishift, set a profile, checkout our Infinipan OpenShift https://github.com/infinispan/infinispan-openshift-templates[repository] and then call:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2018-11-12-the-fastest-path-to-running-infinispan.adoc:37
msgid "oc create -f infinispan-ephemeral.yaml oc new-app infinispan-ephemeral"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2018-11-12-the-fastest-path-to-running-infinispan.adoc:43
msgid "These two simple steps will get you a single node Infinispan Server running! A more detailed getting started guide can be found in the repository's https://github.com/infinispan/infinispan-openshift-templates/blob/master/README.asciidoc[README] file."
msgstr ""

